Realized you're trans? Discovering other general things about your identity? You will likely want a change in your wardrobe. But like most queer individuals, you're poor.

How do you find clothing and accessories on the cheap?

This guide will help you go through how to buy clothes, including how to buy the proper size for you. Ready to look like the hottest punk, or a pretty prince? Let's get started!

## Getting your Measurments

Although there's no universal way of getting your measurements, here's what I've directly copied from [LTT Store](https://lttstore.com), a store with high quality clothes and other products;

- **Chest**: Measure around the widest part of your torso, just under your armpits.
- **Waist**: Measure around the smallest part of your waist, between the top of your hip bone and the base of your rib cage.
- **Hips**: Measure around the fullest part of your hips.
- **Inseam**: Measure from the inside of your leg from the crotch to the bottom of your leg.

